The paper discusses reinforcement learning in mixed-motive games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Social Value Orientation (SVO) to model social preferences suggests a potential fit for social computing (cs.SOC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on population heterogeneity and its effects on behavior aligns with research in social influence (cs.SI).
